31#include "mech_locl.h"
32
33OM_uint32
34_gss_find_mn(OM_uint32 *minor_status, struct _gss_name *name, gss_OID mech,
35 struct _gss_mechanism_name **output_mn)
36{
37 OM_uint32 major_status;
38 gssapi_mech_interface m;
39 struct _gss_mechanism_name *mn;
40
41 *output_mn = NULL;
42
43 HEIM_SLIST_FOREACH(mn, &name->gn_mn, gmn_link) {
44 if (gss_oid_equal(mech, mn->gmn_mech_oid))
45 break;
46 }
47
48 if (!mn) {
49 /*
50 * If this name is canonical (i.e. there is only an
51 * MN but it is from a different mech), give up now.
52 */
53 if (!name->gn_value.value)
54 return GSS_S_BAD_NAME;
55
56 m = __gss_get_mechanism(mech);
57 if (!m)
58 return (GSS_S_BAD_MECH);
59
60 mn = malloc(sizeof(struct _gss_mechanism_name));
61 if (!mn)
62 return GSS_S_FAILURE;
63
64 major_status = m->gm_import_name(minor_status,
65 &name->gn_value,
66 (name->gn_type.elements
67 ? &name->gn_type : GSS_C_NO_OID),
68 &mn->gmn_name);
69 if (major_status != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
70 _gss_mg_error(m, major_status, *minor_status);
71 free(mn);
72 return major_status;
73 }
74
75 mn->gmn_mech = m;
76 mn->gmn_mech_oid = &m->gm_mech_oid;
77 HEIM_SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&name->gn_mn, mn, gmn_link);
78 }
79 *output_mn = mn;
80 return 0;
81}
82
83
84/*
85 * Make a name from an MN.
86 */
87struct _gss_name *
88_gss_make_name(gssapi_mech_interface m, gss_name_t new_mn)
89{
90 struct _gss_name *name;
91 struct _gss_mechanism_name *mn;
92
93 name = malloc(sizeof(struct _gss_name));
94 if (!name)
95 return (0);
96 memset(name, 0, sizeof(struct _gss_name));
97
98 mn = malloc(sizeof(struct _gss_mechanism_name));
99 if (!mn) {
100 free(name);
101 return (0);
102 }
103
104 HEIM_SLIST_INIT(&name->gn_mn);
105 mn->gmn_mech = m;
106 mn->gmn_mech_oid = &m->gm_mech_oid;
107 mn->gmn_name = new_mn;
108 HEIM_SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&name->gn_mn, mn, gmn_link);
109
110 return (name);
111}
